					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.g400.co.uk/cantabits/archives/825#comment-86&quot;&gt;Alastair&lt;/a&gt;.

The clock/weather problem does sound quite bad. &quot;Show Me&quot; doesn&#039;t seem to be present at all in the Android 4.1 update, which solves that problem.

The tasks thing might be fixed in the Android 4.1 update that rolled out recently - I notice that they&#039;ve changed a lot of details of how the tasks work including removing the time they&#039;re due (only the due date remains), grouping by due date in the widget, moving the ability to postpone tasks to a menu (and reducing the postpone options to 1 day and 1 week, as time is no longer relevant) and fixing the format of the due date shown in the widget (see &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.g400.co.uk/cantabits/archives/476#comment-96&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;).

If you&#039;ve set up your phone appropriately, everything should be restored from Google (see things like the &quot;Backup &amp; reset&quot; option in the settings). I haven&#039;t used any backup methods other than this and the methods I gave &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.g400.co.uk/cantabits/archives/825#comment-83&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;above&lt;/a&gt; for a long time, and I consequently wouldn&#039;t be confident in recommending an appropriate app. The descriptions, screenshots and reviews on Google Play are normally sufficiently good quality indicators.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://www.g400.co.uk/cantabits/archives/825#comment-86">Alastair</a>.</p>
<p>The clock/weather problem does sound quite bad. &#8220;Show Me&#8221; doesn&#8217;t seem to be present at all in the Android 4.1 update, which solves that problem.</p>
<p>The tasks thing might be fixed in the Android 4.1 update that rolled out recently &#8211; I notice that they&#8217;ve changed a lot of details of how the tasks work including removing the time they&#8217;re due (only the due date remains), grouping by due date in the widget, moving the ability to postpone tasks to a menu (and reducing the postpone options to 1 day and 1 week, as time is no longer relevant) and fixing the format of the due date shown in the widget (see <a href="http://www.g400.co.uk/cantabits/archives/476#comment-96" rel="nofollow">here</a>).</p>
<p>If you&#8217;ve set up your phone appropriately, everything should be restored from Google (see things like the &#8220;Backup &#038; reset&#8221; option in the settings). I haven&#8217;t used any backup methods other than this and the methods I gave <a href="http://www.g400.co.uk/cantabits/archives/825#comment-83" rel="nofollow">above</a> for a long time, and I consequently wouldn&#8217;t be confident in recommending an appropriate app. The descriptions, screenshots and reviews on Google Play are normally sufficiently good quality indicators.</p>
