The clock/weather problem, if I remember rightly (it&#039;s some time ago now) crashed everytime I tried to access Alarms - this was the one time that factory reset resolved the issue. I was amazed this phone had a bug as soon as I switched it on! But on this occasion HTC support were excellent!

I&#039;m fairly sure the data loss after the &quot;showme&quot; app problem arose from HTC technical support telling me to do a storage delete. It deleted all the data for the &quot;locations&quot; app which I did manage to download again, it also removed all the sample, pictures, music and videos.

The tasks problem arises on my phone when I put a task in the HTC tasks widget, if I have tasks set to display in the calendar it shows 2 copies of each task. HTC claim another factory reset will resolve but I haven&#039;t had time to try it. I&#039;ve got more important things to do than setup my phone again and again. However a good backup program may help me here. I would like to find one that will backup all apps, text messages and settings so I don&#039;t have to spend ages resetting the phone - can you recommend one to do this? I will take another look on Google play to see if I can find something suitable...]]></description>
